cs.GT, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.IT 

The paper deals with learning algorithms for a setting where buyers have combinatorial preferences over items and a seller uses a priority-based allocation mechanism. This falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves the use of algorithms to predict outcomes, which falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper deals with the efficient computation of these algorithms, which falls under information theory (cs.IT).
